GIT: Git is an open source distributed version control system designed to track changes projects with speed and efficiency.

Uses:  
- Free and open source.
- Used for tracking changes in the source code.
- distributed version control system (local repositories can be created).
- multiple people can collaborate and work together.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GitHub: Website to store the repositories online

Uses:
- Provides Backup.
- Provides visual interface of repositories.
- Makes collabartion and sharing easier.
